      "title": "Namaste! (नमस्ते!)",
      "body": "Welcome to Hindi! Hindi is spoken by over 600 million people worldwide. It is written in the Devanagari script, which is phonetic—words are pronounced exactly as they are written.\n\nToday, we will focus on the most important word in Hindi: Namaste (नमस्ते). It means 'Hello', 'Good morning', 'Good afternoon', and 'Goodbye'. It is used in almost every situation to show respect."
